The paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on model-based reinforcement learning, which involves building a model of the environment and using it to plan actions. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of planning and optimization techniques to improve policy learning suggests that the paper could also be classified under robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of temporal difference methods to learn state-dependent model errors suggests that the paper could also be classified under mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
